newsitem.title: UK: European meals prices not quoted owing to holiday.
newsitem.headline: European meals prices not quoted owing to holiday.

text.p: European meal prices were unquoted on Thursday morning with most of Europe closed for the Ascension Day holiday.
UK based brokers said there was talk of increases in the range of $4 to $5 a tonne in high protein soymeal, but were unwilling to give a line up.

"People are saying there is a lot of protection in the market following the higher close in Chicago on Wednesday and increase of $4 to $5 are being talked about, but it's impossible to get a line up," said one said.
